Slice beef into very thin strips. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in medium nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook until browned and juices evaporate, stirring often. Remove beef. Heat remaining oil over medium heat. Add onion and cook until tender-crisp. Add spinach and cook just until spinach is wilted. Add soup and water. Heat to a boil. Return beef to skillet and heat through. Serve beef mixture over tomato. Season to taste with black pepper.